Facilities Use Agreement (Lockhart PV II and CL BESS II; Substation and Interconnection Facilities) This Facilities Use Agreement (Agreement) is made and entered into as of June 2 8, 2024, by and between Lockhart Solar PV II LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (PV ProjectCo), and Lockhart CL ESS II, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (CL BESS ProjectCo, and together with PV ProjectCo, each a ProjectCo, and collectively, the ProjectCos). PV ProjectCo and CL BESS ProjectCo may be referred to herein collectively as the Parties and individually as a Party. RECITALS WHEREAS, PV ProjectCo owns a solar-powered generation facility with an aggregate capacity of approximately 75 MW (the PV Facility) near Hinckley, California. WHEREAS, CL BESS ProjectCo is developing a battery energy storage system with an aggregate capacity of approximately 59.7 MW (the BESS Facility) near Hinckley, California. WHEREAS, the Parties, along with Lockhart Solar PV, LLC, Lockhart CL ESS I, LLC, Lockhart ESS, LLC, Luz Solar Partners Ltd. IX, Lockhart Reserve, LLC and Terra-Gen Operating Company, LLC (TGOC) are parties to that certain Amended and Restated Shared Facilities Agreement (Lockhart Site) (as may be amended and/or restated from time to time, the SFA) that describes the SFA parties rights and obligations regarding certain common infrastructure facilities more particularly described in the SFA, including electrical interconnection facilities (the Shared Facilities). WHEREAS, the Parties, along with Lockhart Solar PV, LLC, Lockhart CL ESS I, LLC, Lockhart ESS, LLC, Lockhart Reserve, LLC, Southern California Edison Company and the California Independent System Operator Corporation are parties to that certain First Amended Large Generator Interconnection Agreement dated October 31, 2023 (as may be amended, the LGIA) that describes the use by the Parties, Lockhart Solar PV, LLC, Lockhart CL ESS I, LLC, Lockhart ESS, LLC and Lockhart Reserve, LLC of the Interconnection Customers Interconnection Facilities (the Interconnection Facilities, and, together with the Shared Facilities, the Joint Use Facilities). WHEREAS, the Parties wish to share the use of their combined portion of the interconnection capacity (Coincident Capacity) of the Joint Use Facilities to deliver the net output of each Facility to the transmission system, and they desire to enter into this Agreement to further document the terms and conditions of such shared use of the Coincident Capacity. NOW, THEREFORE, the parties hereto agree as follows: ARTICLE 1 DEFINITIONS For the purposes of this Agreement, the following words and terms shall have the meanings specified below: Affiliate means, with respect to any Person, any other Person that directly or indirectly, through one or more intermediaries, controls, is controlled by or is under common control with that Person. The term control (including with correlative meaning, the terms controlled by possession, directly or indirectly, of the power to direct or cause the direction of the management and under common control with), as used with respect to any Person, means the and policies of such Person, whether through the ownership of voting securities or membership or partnership interests, by contract or otherwise. Agreement has the meaning given in the preamble. Applicable Law means all laws, treaties, ordinances, statutes, judgments, injunctions, decrees, orders, writs, rules, regulations and interpretations of any Governmental Authority to the extent they apply to the actions of the Parties. "BESS Capacity means the interconnection use rights of CL BESS ProjectCo to use the Joint Use Facilities to deliver the net output of the BESS Facility to the Point of Interconnection pursuant to the LGIA to the extent that the PV Facility is not capable of producing and delivering energy to the Point of Interconnection. BESS Capacity shall include all Deliverability rights and obligations as set forth in the LGIA. BESS Capacity may be referenced as Surplus Interconnection Service under relevant FERC orders. BESS Facility has the meaning given in the Recitals. CAISO means California Independent System Operator Corporation. CL BESS ProjectCo has the meaning given in the preamble. Coincident Capacity has the meaning given in the Recitals. Event of Default has the meaning set forth in Section 6.1 of the Agreement. Facility means the PV Facility or the BESS Facility, as appropriate. FERC means the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. Financing Party means (i) any and all lenders providing senior or subordinated construction, interim or long-term debt financing or refinancing (including hedging counterparties) for the development, construction, purchase or operation of a Facility, and (ii) any and all equity or tax investors providing financing or refinancing of a Facility or purchasing equity ownership interests in a company owning a ProjectCo, including through a lease financing structure, and any trustee or agent acting on behalf of any such lenders, equity or tax investors, or lease equity providers. Force Majeure has the meaning set forth in Section 4.2 of the Agreement. Governmental Authority means any national, state or local government, any political subdivision thereof, or any governmental, quasi-governmental, judicial, public or statutory - 2 - instrumentality, administrative agency, authority, body or other entity having jurisdiction over a Partys operations, or over the Parties. Indemnified Party has the meaning set forth Section 5.1 of the Agreement. Indemnifying Party has the meaning set forth Section 5.1 of the Agreement. Interconnection Facilities has the meaning given in the Recitals. Joint Use Facilities has the meaning given in the Recitals. LGIA has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. Mortgage has the meaning set forth in Section 7.3 of this Agreement. NERC means the North American Electric Reliability Corporation and the applicable regional reliability entity designated by NERC. Person means any individual, corporation, partnership, limited liability company, association, joint stock company, trust, unincorporated organization, joint venture, government or political subdivision or agency therefore, Governmental Authority, or any other entity or organization. PV Facility has the meaning given in the Recitals. PV ProjectCo has the meaning given in the preamble. Prudent Utility Practices means those practices, methods, standards and acts engaged in or approved by a significant portion of the electric industry during the relevant time period, or any of the practices, methods and acts which, in the exercise of reasonable judgment in light of the facts known at the time the decision was made, could have been expected to accomplish the desired result at a reasonable cost consistent with good business practices, reliability, safety and expedition in a manner consistent with Applicable Laws, safety, environmental protection and economy. Prudent Utility Practices are not necessarily defined as the optimal standard practice method or act to the exclusion of others, but rather refer to a range of action reasonable under the circumstances and generally accepted in the region in connection with line taps and the ownership and operation of the facilities and arrangements described in this Agreement. PV Capacity means the interconnection use rights of the PV ProjectCo to use the Joint Use Facilities to deliver the net output of the PV Facility to the Point of Interconnection pursuant to the LGIA, and other ancillary interconnection needs related to 24x7 auxiliary power, facility communications and other requirements necessary for performance under the LGIA, to the extent that the PV Facility is capable of producing and delivering energy to the Point of Interconnection. PV Capacity shall not include charging or delivery of battery stored energy. PV Capacity shall not include Deliverability rights and obligations as set forth in the LGIA. SCE means the Southern California Edison Company. - 3 - SFA has the meaning given in the Recitals. Shared Facilities has the meaning given in the Recitals. TGOC is defined as set forth in the introductory paragraph.
ARTICLE 2 USE OF FACILITIES 2.1 Connection. Each Party shall allow the other Party to use the Coincident Capacity of the Joint Use Facilities as BESS Capacity or PV Capacity, as applicable, and cooperate with the other Party to effectuate such shared use in accordance with Applicable Laws and Prudent Utility Practice. 2.2 Use of the Joint Use Facilities. During the term of this Agreement, each Party will allow the other Party to use the Coincident Capacity of the Joint Use Facilities, as BESS Capacity or PV Capacity, as applicable, to deliver the output of each Partys Facility to: (i) the project site switchyard that connects to the 220 kV transmission line owned by Lockhart Transmission Holdings, LLC (GenTie Co); and (ii) to deliver from such transmission line to the point of interconnection under the LGIA. Each Partys right to use the Coincident Capacity shall be limited to the maximum capacity of each Partys Facility as set forth in the recitals hereto. 2.3 Scheduling. No scheduling services are required for the service provided under this Agreement. Each Party shall make all necessary scheduling arrangements with GenTie Co, Southern California Edison Company and/or the CAISO to accept the output of their respective Facility. 2.4 Availability. Each Party acknowledges that the other Partys rights to access and utilize the Coincident Capacity is essential to the administration, operation and maintenance of both Facilities. Each Party shall comply at all times with the requirements of this Agreement, shall operate and maintain its Facility in accordance with Prudent Utility Practices, and coordinate their use of the Joint Use Facilities and any outages as follows: (a) coordinate with the other Party with respect to scheduling any planned outages of its Facility and the Joint Use Facilities with the goal of scheduling planned outages during periods which minimize the impact on each Facilitys operations. (b) shall give notice to the other Parties as soon as possible of any unplanned outages of its Facility and shall work to restore its Facility to service as quickly as possible. (c) The Parties shall adopt operating assumptions (the Operating Assumptions) that reflect the proposed charging and discharge behavior of the CL BESS ProjectCo in a manner that is consistent with its BESS Capacity, the terms and conditions of the LGIA, and the requirements and guidelines of CAISO, SCE, NERC and any other entity with authority over the operations of the Parties. If required under the LGIA or by SCE or CAISO, the Parties shall provide such Operating Assumptions to SCE and CAISO. For the avoidance of - 4 - doubt, the ProjectCos may operate at the same time, with the PV Project Co having priority pursuant to the terms set forth in the LGIA. (d) The Parties shall direct any third-party providing operations and maintenance, scheduling or other services to perform in a manner consistent with the Operating Assumptions and the terms of this Agreement, including under any offtake agreement in which the offtaker controls the scheduling of the resource. (e) The CL BESS ProjectCo may use the Joint Use Facilities to charge BESS Facility at any time without any limitation under this Agreement; provided, however, that the CL BESS ProjectCo shall limit its charging activities in accordance with the LGIA and the requirements and guidelines of CAISO, SCE, NERC and any other entity with authority over its operations. (f) The Parties anticipate that the CL BESS ProjectCo will not often use the Joint Use Facilities to discharge the BESS Facility in a manner that would cause the PV ProjectCo to curtail the PV Facility; provided, however, that: (i) no Party shall be obligated to take any action that could result in a violation of a CAISO or SCE tariff; (ii) each Party shall operate its Facility in accordance with all dispatch orders issued by the CAISO; (iii) the Parties acknowledge and agree that BESS Capacity includes Deliverability rights under the LGIA, which may result in CAISO directing the CL BESS ProjectCo to discharge the BESS Facility despite the PV ProjectCos rights to use its PV Capacity during such CAISO direction; and (iv) the CL BESS ProjectCo shall reimburse the PV ProjectCo for lost revenue and production tax credits as set forth in the SFA. 2.5 Curtailment. Each Partys use of the Coincident Capacity of the Joint Use Facilities may be subject to curtailment to the extent necessary for maintenance to maintain reliable operation of the Joint Use Facilities. Charges. No charges will be assessed in connection with the Parties shared use of the Coincident Capacity. Each Party shall be responsible for its share of all expenses necessary for the operation and maintenance of the Joint Use Facilities and any charges associated with maintaining this Agreement on file with FERC.Notwithstanding the foregoing, in no event shall a ProjectCo be responsible for more than its share of expenses due under the SFA or LGIA. ARTICLE 3TERM AND TERMINATION 3.1 Term. Service under this Agreement shall commence upon or after the date specified by FERC, and shall continue in effect until terminated by (a) mutual agreement of the Parties or (b) pursuant to Section 3.2 or 6.1(b). 3.2 Termination. This Agreement shall terminate (i) upon the date that either Party, or its successors and assigns, have permanently ceased operation of its Facility, or (ii) if a Party transfers all of its ownership interest in the Joint Use Facilities, and this Agreement is not assigned in accordance with Section 7.1. 3.3 Governmental Approvals for Termination. Notwithstanding anything in this Agreement to the contrary, termination shall not become effective until the Parties have complied - 5 - with all Applicable Laws applicable to such termination, including obtaining any necessary FERC authorizations for such termination. 3.4 Survival Rights. Termination of this Agreement (a) shall not relieve any Party of any obligation hereunder which expressly or by implication survives termination hereof, including all indemnity obligations, and (b) except as otherwise provided in any provision of this Agreement expressly limiting the liability of a Party, shall not relieve a Party of any obligations or liabilities for loss or damage to the other Parties arising out of or caused by any breach of this Agreement by such Party prior to the effectiveness of such termination or arising out of such termination. ARTICLE 4-- FORCE MAJEURE 4.1 Excuse. No Party shall be considered in default under this Agreement for any delay or failure in the performance of its obligations and shall be excused in the performance of its obligations under this Agreement if such delay or failure is due to an event of Force Majeure. 4.2 Definition. Force Majeure means any event or circumstance, including any of the following enumerated events, that occur before the termination of this Agreement and that delays or prevents a Partys performance of its obligations under this Agreement, but only to the extent that (a) such event of Force Majeure is not attributable to fault or negligence on the part of such Party, (b) such event of Force Majeure is caused by factors beyond such Partys reasonable control; and (c) despite taking all reasonable technical and commercial precautions and measures to prevent, avoid, mitigate or overcome such event and the consequences thereof, such Party affected has been unable to prevent, avoid, mitigate or overcome such event or consequences: (a) Acts of God such as epidemic, pandemic, storms, hurricanes, floods, lightning and earthquakes; (b) Sabotage or destruction by a third-party of facilities and equipment relating to the performance by the affected Party of its obligations under this Agreement; (c) War, riot, acts of a public enemy or other civil disturbance; (d) Strike, walkout, lockout or other significant labor dispute; or (e) Action or inaction of a Governmental Authority. 4.3 Conditions. A Party may rely on a claim of Force Majeure to excuse its performance only to the extent that such Party: (a) Provides prompt notice of such Force Majeure event to the other Parties, giving an estimate of its expected duration and the probable impact on the performance of its obligations under this Agreement; (b) Exercises all reasonable efforts to continue to perform its obligations under this Agreement; - 6 - (c) Expeditiously takes action to correct or cure the event or condition excusing performance so that the suspension of performance is no greater in scope and no longer in duration than is dictated by the event or condition being corrected or cured using commercially reasonable efforts; provided, however, that settlement of strikes or other labor disputes will be completely within the sole discretion of the Party affected by such strike or labor dispute; (d) Exercises all commercially reasonable efforts to mitigate or limit damages to the other Parties; and (e) Provides prompt notice to the other Parties of the cessation of the event or condition giving rise to its excuse from performance. ARTICLE 5-- INDEMNIFICATION 5.1 General Indemnity. Each Party (the Indemnifying Party) shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless the other Party and their directors, managers, officers, agents, employees, successors and assigns (each, an Indemnified Party) from and against any and all suits, actions, legal or administrative proceedings, claims, demands, costs (including reasonable attorneys fees) and expenses (each a Claim) of any nature for death or personal injury to any person or physical damage to the property of third parties arising from (i) a negligent (whether active or passive) act or omission or the willful misconduct of the Indemnifying Party, or its contractors, or their respective employees or agents; or (ii) any failure of the Indemnifying Party to comply with Applicable Law in connection with this Agreement; except to the extent such Claim arise from the negligence or willful misconduct of an Indemnified Party. 5.2 Indemnification Procedure. When required to indemnify an Indemnified Party, the Indemnifying Party shall assume on behalf of such Indemnified Party and conduct with due diligence and in good faith the defense of any Claim against such party, whether or not the Indemnifying Party shall be joined therein, and the Indemnified Party shall cooperate with the Indemnifying Party in such defense. The Indemnifying Party shall have charge and direction of the defense and settlement of such Claim; provided, however, that without relieving the Indemnifying Party of its obligations hereunder or impairing the Indemnifying Partys right to control the defense or settlement thereof, the Indemnified Party may elect to participate through separate counsel in the defense of any such Claim, but the fees and expenses of such counsel shall be at the expense of such Indemnified Party unless (a) the counsel employed by such Indemnified Party shall have reasonably concluded that there exists a material conflict of interest between the Indemnifying Party and such Indemnified Party in the conduct of the defense of such Claim (in which case the Indemnifying Party shall not have the right to control the defense or settlement of such claim on behalf of such Indemnified Party), or (b) the Indemnifying Party shall not have employed counsel to assume the defense of such Claim within a reasonable time after notice of the commencement thereof. In each of such cases the fees and expenses of counsel shall be at the expense of the Indemnifying Party. ARTICLE 6-- TERMINATION FOR DEFAULT 6.1 Event of Default - 7 - (a) A Party shall be in default under this Agreement (an Event of Default) if such Party fails to perform in any material respect any of its obligations under this Agreement, the SFA, the LGIA or the LGIA Co-Tenancy Agreement. (b) A Party may terminate this Agreement upon an Event of Default by another Party (i) if such Event of Default is not cured within thirty (30) days after receipt of such Partys written notice to the defaulting Party, or (ii) if such Event of Default is not a payment default and can be cured but not within the aforesaid thirty (30) day period, corrective action is not commenced within thirty (30) days after receipt of such Partys written notice to the defaulting Party and the defaulting Party does not thereafter diligently pursue such cure and complete the cure within a reasonable period of time. (c) Consequences of Termination. Upon termination by a Party for an Event of Default, each non-defaulting Party shall be entitled to all legal and equitable remedies that are not expressly prohibited or limited by the terms of this Agreement. ARTICLE 7 ASSIGNMENTS AND TRANSFERS 7.1 General Restriction. Neither Party shall transfer or assign this Agreement without the other Partys prior written consent; provided, however, that each Party shall have the right to assign this Agreement (i) if a transfer of the assigning Partys rights under the SFA and LGIA is permitted by such agreements, and (ii) such assignment of this Agreement is accompanied by an assignment of the assigning Partys rights under the SFA and LGIA. When duly assigned in accordance with the foregoing, this Agreement shall be binding upon and shall inure to the benefit of the assignee; any other assignment shall be void and without force or effect. Any other assignment shall be void and without force or effect. 7.2 Right to Encumber. Notwithstanding anything in Section 7.1 to the contrary, each Party may, at any time and from time to time during the term of this Agreement, encumber, mortgage or hypothecate to any Financing Party by a security or similar agreement, (the Mortgage) all or part of its interest under this Agreement and the other documents entered into in connection with this Agreement, including, without limitation, the SFA, without the consent of the other Party hereto. Should a Party incur any encumbrance in accordance with this Section 7.2, and should the Parties receive notice thereof, the Parties hereby expressly stipulate and agree between themselves and on behalf of, and for the benefit of, the Financing Party as follows: (a) Modification of Agreement. They will not modify this Agreement or allow this Agreement to be modified in any way nor cancel this Agreement without the written consent of the Financing Party, which consent may not be unreasonably withheld or delayed. (b) Performance by Financing Party. The Financing Party shall have the right to do any act or thing required of the assigning Party under this Agreement, and any such act or thing performed by the Financing Party shall be as effective to prevent a default under this Agreement and/or a forfeiture of any of the assigning Partys rights under this Agreement as if done by the assigning Party itself, provided that the Financing Party shall have first given the the assigning Party such notice and allowed the assigning Party to perform or attempt to perform such act or thing for such period - 8 - of time as may be specified in any documents or instruments executed by the assigning Party for the benefit of the Financing Party. The Financing Party shall have such foreclosure and sale rights and rights to perform or cause to be performed the covenants and agreements of the assigning Party under this Agreement as may be specified in any documents or instruments executed by the assigning Party for the benefit of the Financing Party. (c) Notice to Financing Party. If any Party issues or receives any notices regarding potential or actual defaults as described herein, the assigning Party shall as soon as practicable deliver a copy of such notice to all Financing Parties of which it has received notice. (d) Consents to Assignment. Each Party hereby agrees that it shall, no later than five (5) business days after a request by the other Party (or its Financing Party), execute such consents or estoppel certificates as are reasonably requested by the other Party or its Financing Party. ARTICLE 8 REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES 8.1 CL BESS ProjectCo Representations. CL BESS ProjectCo represents and warrants that: (a) Organization. CL BESS ProjectCo is a limited liability company duly organized, validly existing and in good standing under the laws of the State of Delaware, and is qualified to do business in all jurisdictions in which the nature of the business conducted by it makes such qualification necessary and where failure to so qualify would have a material adverse effect on its ability to perform this Agreement. (b) No Violation of Law; Litigation. CL BESS ProjectCo is not in violation of any Applicable Laws, or judgment entered by any Governmental Authority which violations, individually or in the aggregate, would materially and adversely affect its performance of any obligations under this Agreement. (c) Company Action. CL BESS ProjectCo has all necessary power and authority to execute, deliver and perform its obligations under this Agreement; the execution, delivery and performance by CL BESS ProjectCo of this Agreement have been duly authorized by all necessary limited liability company action on its part; and, this Agreement has been duly and validly executed and delivered by CL BESS ProjectCo and constitutes the legal, valid and binding obligation of CL BESS ProjectCo enforceable in accordance with its terms, except as the enforceability thereof may be limited by bankruptcy, insolvency, reorganization or moratorium or other similar laws relating to the enforcement of creditors rights generally and by general equitable principles. 8.2 PV ProjectCo Representations. PV ProjectCo represents and warrants that: (a) Organization. PV ProjectCo is a limited liability company duly organized, validly existing and in good standing under the laws of the State of Delaware, and is qualified to do business in all jurisdictions in which the nature of the business conducted by it makes such - 9 - qualification necessary and where failure to so qualify would have a material adverse effect on its ability to perform this Agreement. (b) No Violation of Law; Litigation. PV ProjectCo is not in violation of any Applicable Laws or judgment entered by any Governmental Authority, which violations, individually or in the aggregate, would materially and adversely affect its performance of any obligations under this Agreement. (c) Company Action. PV ProjectCo has all necessary power and authority to execute, deliver and perform its obligations under this Agreement; the execution, delivery and performance by PV ProjectCo of this Agreement have been duly authorized by all necessary action on its part; and, this Agreement has been duly and validly executed and delivered by PV ProjectCo and constitutes the legal, valid and binding obligation of PV ProjectCo enforceable in accordance with its terms, except as the enforceability thereof may be limited by bankruptcy, insolvency, reorganization or moratorium or other similar laws relating to the enforcement of creditors rights generally and by general equitable principles. ARTICLE 9 DISPUTE RESOLUTION 9.1 Governing Law; Jurisdiction. This Agreement is governed by the laws of the State of California, excluding any choice of law rules that would direct application of laws of another jurisdiction. Each Party hereby irrevocably and unconditionally submits to the exclusive jurisdiction of any California State court or federal court of the United States of America sitting in Los Angeles, and waives, to the fullest extent legally permissible, any objection which it may now or hereafter have to the personal jurisdiction of such courts or venue of any proceeding arising out of or relating to this Agreement in such courts and any defense of an inconvenient forum to the maintenance of such action or proceeding in such courts. 9.2 Jury Trial Waiver. EACH PARTY HEREBY WAIVES, TO THE FULLEST EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, ANY RIGHT IT MAY HAVE TO A TRIAL BY JURY IN RESPECT OF ANY LITIGATION DIRECTLY OR INDIRECTLY ARISING OUT OF, UNDER OR IN CONNECTION WITH THIS AGREEMENT. ARTICLE 10 LIMITATION OF LIABILITY 10.1 Consequential Damages. EXCEPT IN CASES OF FRAUD OR WILLFUL MISCONDUCT, NO PARTY SHALL BE LIABLE FOR ANY PUNITIVE, EXEMPLARY, CONSEQUENTIAL OR SPECIAL DAMAGES THAT ARISE OUT OF, RELATE TO, OR ARE OTHERWISE ATTRIBUTABLE TO THIS AGREEMENT OR THE PERFORMANCE OR NON-PERFORMANCE OF SERVICES, OR ANY ADDITIONAL SERVICES, OR OTHER DUTIES HEREUNDER, EXCEPT TO THE EXTENT SUCH DAMAGES ARE OWED TO UNAFFILIATED THIRD PARTIES IN RELATION TO A LOSS FOR WHICH ONE PARTY OWES INDEMNITY OBLIGATIONS TO ANOTHER PARTY UNDER THIS AGREEMENT. FOR AVOIDANCE OF DOUBT, LOST REVENUES FROM LOST PRODUCTION OR PRODUCTION RESULTING FROM AN OUTAGE, DISCONNECTION, OR DAMAGE TO A PROJECT SHALL NOT BE CONSIDERED CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES HEREUNDER, AND SHALL BE FULLY RECOVERABLE DAMAGES FOR ANY CLAIMS ARISING HEREUNDER. - 10 - 10.2 Releases Valid in All Events. Releases, disclaimers and limitations on liability expressed herein shall apply even in the event of the negligence, strict liability, fault or breach of contract (including other legal bases of responsibility such as fundamental breach) of the Party whose liability is released, disclaimed or limited to the extent provided in such release, disclaimer and limitation and shall inure to the benefit of the released Partys Affiliates. ARTICLE 11 GENERAL PROVISIONS 11.1 Notices. Any notice required or authorized to be given hereunder or any other communications between the Parties shall be in writing (unless otherwise provided) and shall be served personally or by reputable express courier service or by facsimile transmission addressed to the relevant Party at the address stated below or at any other address notified by such Party to the other Parties as its address for service. Any notice so given personally shall be deemed to have been served on delivery, any notice so given by express courier service shall be deemed to have been served two (2) working days after the same shall have been delivered to the relevant courier, and any notice so given by facsimile transmission shall be deemed to have been served on dispatch; provided that such facsimile notice is transmitted during business hours in the primary recipients location (which, for purposes of this Section 11.1, shall mean any time before 5:00 p.m. on a day that is not a Saturday, Sunday or legal holiday in the state where such recipient is located) and otherwise shall be deemed to have been served upon the commencement of the next succeeding business hours in the recipients location. As proof of such service it shall be sufficient to produce a receipt showing personal service, the receipt of a reputable courier company showing the correct address of the addressee or an activity report of the senders facsimile machine showing the correct facsimile number of the Party on whom notice is served and the correct number of pages transmitted and the date of dispatch. The Parties addresses for service are as follows, although each Party may change its address for service by written notice to the other Parties given as provided in this Section 11.1: If to PV ProjectCo: c/o Terra-Gen, LLC nd 437 Madison Ave., 22 Floor New York, NY 10022 Attention: Chief Financial Officer If to CL BESS ProjectCo: c/o Terra-Gen, LLC nd 437 Madison Ave., 22 Floor New York, NY 10022 Attention: Senior Vice President - Operations 11.2 Change of Notice Recipient Information. Any Party may, by giving notice at any time or from time to time, require subsequent notice to be given to another individual, whether a Party or an officer or representative of a Party, or to a different address, or both. Notices given before actual receipt of notice of change shall not be invalidated by the change. - 11 - 11.3 Amendment. This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement among the parties pertaining to the subject matter hereof and supersedes all prior agreements, representations, communications and understandings, written or oral, express or implied, pertaining thereto. Any changes to this Agreement shall require the written approval of the Parties (not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed) and the Financing Party pursuant to Section 7.3(a) and shall be subject to FERC approval. 11.4 Construction. The language in all parts of this Agreement shall be in all cases construed simply according to its fair meaning and not strictly for or against any of the Parties hereto. 11.5 Validity. Should any portion of this Agreement be declared invalid and unenforceable, then such portion shall be deemed to be severable from this Agreement and shall not affect the remainder hereof; and the Parties shall negotiate in good faith to replace such invalid and unenforceable provision. 11.6 Waiver. The failure of a Party at any time to require performance by another Party of any provision hereof shall not affect in any way the full right to require such performance at any time thereafter, nor shall the waiver by a Party of any breach of any provision hereof be held or deemed to be a waiver of the provision itself. 11.7 Third-Party Beneficiaries. Except for provisions (including indemnity, limitation of liability, waiver and release provisions) that are expressly stated as inuring for the benefit of a Partys Affiliates or its directors, managers, officers, agents, employees, successors and assigns, the provisions of this Agreement are intended for the sole benefit of each ProjectCo and the Financing Party, and there are no third-party beneficiaries other than assignees contemplated by the terms herein. 11.8 Further Assurances. Each Party agrees to provide such information, execute and deliver any instruments and documents and take such other actions as may be necessary or reasonably requested by another Party that are not inconsistent with the provisions of this Agreement and that do not involve the assumption of obligations other than those provided for in this Agreement, in order to give full effect to this Agreement and to carry out the intent of this Agreement. 11.9 Counterparts. This Agreement may be executed in any number of counterparts and by each of the Parties in separate counterparts, each of which when so executed shall be deemed to be an original and all of which taken together shall constitute one and the same Agreement.
